{{Infobox person | name = Thor O. Hannevig | image = | caption = | birth_name = Thor Olaf Hannevig | birth_date = {{Birth date|1891|4|20|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Åsgårdstrand]], Norway | death_date = {{Death date and age|1975|2|17|1891|4|20|df=y}} | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|display=inline}} --> | monuments = In [[Vinje]] (1991) | residence = | nationality = Norwegian | other_names = | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = Shipmaster | years_active = | employer = | organization = | agent = | known_for = [[Battle of Vinjesvingen]] | notable_works = | style = | home_town = | television = | religion = | spouse = | partner = | children = | parents = | relatives = | awards = }} '''Thor Olaf Hannevig''' (20 April 1891 &ndash; 17 February 1975) was a Norwegian shipmaster. During the [[Norwegian Campaign]] in 1940 he was in command of an army unit called the ''Telemark Infantry Regiment'', and this regiment was able to [[Battle of Vinjesvingen|withstand the German forces until 5 May]]. Hannevig later acquired a legendary heroic status, and his story was the basis of the 1993 Norwegian film ''[[The Last Lieutenant]]''.<ref name=nkl>{{cite encyclopedia |last=Kraglund |first=Ivar |authorlink=Ivar Kraglund |encyclopedia=[[Norsk krigsleksikon 1940–1945]] |title=Hannevig, Thor 0. |language=Norwegian |editor=[[Hans Fredrik Dahl|Dahl]] |editor2=[[Guri Hjeltnes|Hjeltnes]] |editor3=[[Berit Nøkleby|Nøkleby]] |editor4=[[Nils Johan Ringdal|Ringdal]] |editor5=[[Øystein Sørensen|Sørensen]] |url=http://www.nb.no/nbsok/nb/d2e8afecb1aba47bf48bb3cd246dd070?index=0#0 |page=158 |accessdate=18 April 2013 |year=1995 |publisher=Cappelen |location=Oslo |isbn=82-02-14138-9 }}</ref><ref name=vinjesvingen>{{cite encyclopedia |last=Kraglund |first=Ivar | encyclopedia=[[Norsk krigsleksikon 1940–1945]] |title=Vinjesvingen |language=Norwegian |editor=[[Hans Fredrik Dahl|Dahl]] |editor2=[[Guri Hjeltnes|Hjeltnes]] |editor3=[[Berit Nøkleby|Nøkleby]] |editor4=[[Nils Johan Ringdal|Ringdal]] |editor5=[[Øystein Sørensen|Sørensen]] |url=http://www.nb.no/nbsok/nb/d2e8afecb1aba47bf48bb3cd246dd070?index=0#0 |pages=441–442 |accessdate=18 April 2013 |year=1995 |publisher=Cappelen |location=Oslo |isbn=82-02-14138-9 }}</ref>
Hannevig was born in [[Åsgårdstrand]]. He had taken an 8-months' officer's course in 1915. In addition to being a shipmaster, during his life he also owned a distillery, was an adventurer and a Freemason, and worked in a hotel, as a banker, a merchant, and a farmer. He died in [[Skreia]] in 1975. A monument was erected in [[Vinje]] to mark the centenary of his birth in 1991.<ref>{{cite web |first=Harald |last=Huse |url=http://www.mil.no/start/aktuelt/nyheter/article.jhtml?articleID=74771 |title=Thor Olaf Hannevig 1891 - 1975 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930212140/http://www.mil.no/start/aktuelt/nyheter/article.jhtml?articleID=74771 |date=13 January 2004 |language=Norwegian |website=Forsvarsnett |archivedate=30 September 2007 }}</ref>
